<p>We repair LG dryers across Woodland Hills — same-day in most cases, typically a 2–3 hour response, and $280–380 for the common fixes. This is the hottest corner of the Valley, so the call we get most is a no-heat dryer when a summer heatwave tips a thermal fuse on a ranch-home vent that's slowly clogged for years. Our LG Dryer Repair techs clear the vent and confirm the fault before they quote — call (323) 990-7550.</p>
<p>Woodland Hills is the far western end of the San Fernando Valley — and it runs hot. July and August temperatures out here regularly hit 105–108°F, and the LA County all-time heat record of 121°F was set right here in September 2020. That heat matters for LG dryer maintenance in a specific way that we explain to every Woodland Hills customer. The ranch-style homes that make up most of this city — built in the 1960s and 1970s on streets like Shoup Avenue, Dumetz Road, and Oxnard Street — have vent runs that have been quietly accumulating lint for decades. When the temperature climbs to 105°F and a dryer with a 65% blocked vent runs a cycle, the thermal fuse has nowhere left to go. We get the call. The machine is almost always fine. The vent was the problem — and the summer heat was the last straw.</p>
